 Dutywa police are investigating case of culpable homicide after an unidentified man was killed in an accident on Thursday. “It is alleged that a man, who is believed to be 30 years old, was hit by a motor vehicle,” said police spokesperson, Captain Jackson Manatha. “The accident occurred on Thursday, at about 19:45, along N2 highway near Canca forest Dutywa. “The deceased died at the scene.” Captain Manatha said that the cause of the accident is under investigation by Dutywa Police detectives. “Anyone who wishes to identify the deceased can contact Dutywa Police at 047 489 1333.” 